modules.description: Implements functions to generate F#-compatible binary serialization and deserialization code for OCaml types. Works with OCaml type declarations and produces structure items that can be integrated into modules. Used to bridge data serialization between OCaml and F# systems, ensuring type-safe binary data exchange.

Implements binary serialization and deserialization for OCaml types using ppx derivers. Works directly with OCaml type definitions to generate efficient bin_io implementations. Used to enable high-performance binary data exchange between OCaml programs or with external systems like F# through the For_f_sharp submodule.

This module generates code for serializing and deserializing OCaml values based on their type definitions. It provides functions to derive shape and digest expressions for core types, used in binary serialization libraries. The module works with OCaml's type declarations, structures, and signatures to produce low-level serialization logic directly from type definitions.
